<h2 class='comment-title'><div class='status-alert float-right bug-status open'>open</div><a href='/pmwiki/query.php?parent_id=95491&type=wl' class='title bold'>New Trope Repair Shop rationale: YMMV</a></h2>
<p>As you may recall, it was decided sometime in 2014 that deciding whether a page should be classified as <a class='twikilink' href='/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/YMMV/HomePage' title='/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/YMMV/HomePage'>YMMV</a> should be handled in the <a class='twikilink' href='/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Administrivia/TropeRepairShop' title='/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Administrivia/TropeRepairShop'>Trope Repair Shop</a>. Therefore, I think that when creating a new thread there should be a reason about possible subjectivity, perhaps simply called "YMMV".
</p>
<div class='footer'><div class='button-group skinny font-s float-right'><a href="#upvote" data-modal-target="login" data-query-id="95491"><i class="fa fa-thumbs-up"></i> <span class="count">2</span></a><a href='/pmwiki/query.php?parent_id=95491&type=wl'>3 replies <i class='fa fa-chevron-right font-xs'></i></a></div></div>
