<h2 class='comment-title'><div class='status-alert float-right bug-status open'>open</div><a href='/pmwiki/query.php?parent_id=95564&type=wl' class='title bold'>Button on queries to warn that an answer is being written</a></h2>
<p>I think there should be a button that'd be next to each query in query.php boards, where if you press it, the words "[Tropername] is writing an answer" are shown below the query's text. I think it should in some way force a refresh for all users on that specific query to make sure other people considering writing an answer notice. Of course, to prevent trolling or otherwise disruption, it should have a time limit of 10 minutes before it has to be renewed, like how the edit screen has a limit of 20 minutes. This would help with annoying cases like <a class='urllink' href='https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/query.php?parent_id=95563&amp;type=att'>this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;" /></a>. If you add this feature, thank you.
</p>
<span class="edited-by">Edited by Piterpicher</span>
