<div class="comment">
<h2 class='comment-title'><div class='status-alert float-right bug-status open'>open</div><a href='/pmwiki/query.php?parent_id=94828&type=wl' class='title bold'>Note tags need to be closed or the page won't save.</a></h2>
<p>So, the problem is that if a troper adds a [[note]] tag to a page and then forgets to add the closing tag, then the page breaks and appears blank. I've seen quite a few <a class='twikilink' style="color:#D2691E;" href='/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AskTheTropers'>Ask The Tropers</a> threads complaining about mysteriously blank pages and this is always the culprit.
</p><p>I think it would be a good idea to have a bit of scripting so that if you try to save a page that has an unclosed note tag, then it stops you and gives you a warning message to close the note tag before you save your edit.
</p>
<div class='footer'><div class='button-group skinny font-s float-right'><a href="#upvote" data-modal-target="login" data-query-id="94828"><i class="fa fa-thumbs-up"></i> <span class="count">5</span></a><a href='/pmwiki/query.php?parent_id=94828&type=wl'>0 replies <i class='fa fa-chevron-right font-xs'></i></a></div></div>
